The paper deals with domain adaptation in natural language processing (NLP), which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a neural network model that combines ideas from two prominent strands of research on domain adaptation through representation learning, which suggests that it could fall under the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) or "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI).
